The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, (NDLEA) Osun State Command has seized 19.3kg of Indian hemp at a farm in Osun State. The Commander of NDLEA in Osun, Mr Egbeola Samuel confirmed this in a chat with Daily Trust in Osogbo today. The NDLEA boss said there are more cannabis sativa farms in different location in the state that have been identified and would be destroyed as soon as the command gets supports form the state government. Egbeola commended the state governor, Mr Rauf Aregbesola for assisting the command and vowed that the NDLEA Osun would not relent in its efforts to rid the state of Indian hemp and other illicit drugs. Details later